  "body": "\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf we query a non-existed block using `/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/{block_id}` API,\r\n-  As the [spec](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/#/Beacon/getBlockV2) described, prysm endpoint should returns status code `404` , with mesage: `{ \"code\": 400,\"message\": \"Invalid block ID: current\"}`\r\n- But `v3.1.1` will return status code `500`, with message: `{\"message\":\"GetBlockV2: rpc error: code = NotFound desc = Could not find requested block: signed beacon block can't be nil\",\"code\":500}`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n`curl localhost:3500/eth/v2/beacon/blocks/4716680`\r\n\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\nv3.1.1 returns http status code `500` and message is  : <pre><code>\r\n{\r\n\"message\":\"GetBlockV2: rpc error: code = NotFound desc = Could not find requested block: signed beacon block can't be nil\",\r\n\"code\":500\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\nSpec returns http status code`404` and message is : <pre><code>\r\n{\r\n  \"code\": 400,\r\n  \"message\": \"Invalid block ID: current\"\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\nv3.1.1\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n",
